    "Supervised Learning approaches can be commonly listed based on the algorithm as Naïve Bayes, SVM, Decision Tree, Random Forests and ANN (Fig. 10).",
    "Supervised learning necessitates labelling the data before the training process.",
    "During the training process, the training examples are input into the model.",
    "The model output predictions are compared against the label (true) value.",
    "The difference between the model prediction and the label is used to form a cost function."
